    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sorted 2003 BMW M3 (E46), a benchmark in longitudinal front-engine, rear-drive dynamics. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L straight-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double-VANOS variable valve timing to achieve a linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a precise 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and a torque-sensing limited-slip differential. The suspension geometry remains tight, offering the telepathic turn-in and mid-corner stability these chassis are renowned for. This example has undergone preventative maintenance on critical areas including the VANOS hub and subframe reinforcement. While presenting with minor cosmetic patina reflecting its status as a dedicated driver\u2019s car, the drivetrain and structural integrity remain excellent.",
